-- Hungary to Exempt Central Bank From Transaction Tax, Nemzet Says
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-08-07T07:10:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/hungary-to-exempt-central-bank-from-transaction-tax-nemzet-says.html
Hungary ’s government is working on
amending the 2013 budget to exempt the central bank from a
financial-transaction tax that has sparked international
criticism,  Magyar Nemzet  newspaper said, without saying how it
obtained the information.  Under the changes, which may be completed by the end of
next week, the Cabinet will implement spending cuts to replace
an estimated 120 billion forint ($539 million) in  tax revenue ,
according to Nemzet.  The Economy Ministry didn’t confirm that the government was
planning to exempt the Magyar Nemzeti Bank from paying the levy,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
